# Cursor Rules Configuration

# General behavior rules
- Always use TypeScript
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- No incline comments
- Use pure functions where possible
- Use functional components instead of class components
- Use /src/components directory for components
- Use /src/screens directory for screens
- Use zustand for state management
- Use react-native-reanimated for animations
- Don't use View, Button, Text, TextInput, StyleSheet, TouchableOpacity, Pressable from react-native

# File organization rules
- Focus on colocation of code

<!-- # Testing rules
- Tests should be in __tests__ directory
- Write tests for new features
- Maintain test coverage above 80%
- Use Jest for unit tests
- Use React Testing Library for component tests -->

# Security rules
- Never commit sensitive information
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Validate all user inputs
- Sanitize data before rendering

<!-- # Performance rules
- Optimize bundle size
- Use proper caching strategies
- Implement lazy loading where appropriate
- Monitor and optimize render performance -->

# Accessibility rules
- Follow WCAG 2.1 guidelines
- Include proper ARIA attributes
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain sufficient color contrast

# Git rules
- Write clear commit messages
- Create feature branches for new work
- Keep commits atomic and focused
- Review code before merging
